pwd(print working directory)
It displays the current working directory.

dir(windows)/ls(linux)
It lists all the files and folders of current working directory.

cd(Current directory)
It moves to the parent directory.

mkdir(Make directory)
It creates a new folder.

rmdir
To remove an empty folder.

cls(windows)/clear(linux)
clear the command prompt screen.

echo 
It prints the text or the value of environment variables.
Ex- echo Hello

tree
It displays the directory structure in a tree format.

type(windows)/cat(linux)
It displays the content of a text file.
Example: type notes.txt
Output: Hello Java

copy(windows)/cp(linux)
Copies a file from one location to another.
Ex -copy resume.pdf backup.pdf

ren(windows)/mv(linux)
It is used to rename the file or folder.
Ex -ren test.txt notes.txt

del(windows)/rm(linux)
It is used to delete a file.
Ex -del notes.txt

touch
It is used to create new file.
Ex - touch index.html

find 
It is used to search file or folder.
Ex - file . -name "index.html"

grep 
It is used to search text inside the file.
Ex - grep "Hello" index.html

history
Displays the list of previously executed commands.











